-- Uganda Boat Accident Kills at Least 70 People, 17 Rescued, Vision Reports
-- Fred Ojambo
-- 2010-08-02T06:23:04Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-08-02/uganda-boat-accident-kills-at-least-70-people-17-rescued-vision-reports.html

          
          
             At least 70 people may have died
after their boat capsized on July 31 in Lake Albert in the
north-western district of Hoima,  Uganda ,  New Vision , citing
survivors and the police.  
 Another 17 people were rescued from the boat, which was
overloaded with traders, school children, fish and luggage when
the accident happened, the Kampala-based newspaper reported.  
 To contact the reporter on this story:
 Fred Ojambo  in Kampala via Johannesburg at
   vwessels@bloomberg.net .  
          
          


  


        